This paper deals with the secure and reliable connectivity of wireless sensor networks, which is a topic that falls under the categories of computer security (cs.CR) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also involves the use of random graphs and probabilistic analysis, which are topics in theoretical computer science (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper discusses practical applications of the results, which could fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
